1
00:00:56,490 --> 00:00:58,610
Please wait here, sir.

2
00:00:59,390 --> 00:01:02,660
Thanks. You didn't have to come all the way here.

3
00:01:02,660 --> 00:01:04,970
That wouldn't be right, Ms. Ko.

4
00:01:04,970 --> 00:01:08,350
I brought you back from an outside business trip.

5
00:01:08,350 --> 00:01:10,320
Go on in. I'll just take this home.

6
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:12,810
Okay. Get home safe.

7
00:01:14,640 --> 00:01:16,310
Unni!

8
00:01:16,910 --> 00:01:19,200
- Ho Suk.
- You haven't heard yet, right?

9
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:21,530
Se Ri called earlier.

10
00:01:21,530 --> 00:01:23,940
Her father has gone missing.

11
00:01:23,940 --> 00:01:25,040
What?

12
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:26,850
Se Ri was crying her eyes out,

13
00:01:26,850 --> 00:01:28,500
and Mother called Yudanhwa Cosmetics

14
00:01:28,500 --> 00:01:31,340
and yelled at them to find Seong Man Ok-

15
00:01:31,340 --> 00:01:33,350
Yeong Rye! Take this taxi.

16
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:51,060
Jae Pil!

17
00:01:53,160 --> 00:01:54,430
Se Ri!

18
00:01:54,430 --> 00:01:57,040
- Unni!
- Yeong Rye.

19
00:01:57,640 --> 00:01:58,990
Ahjumma.

20
00:01:59,590 --> 00:02:01,960
What happened? Where's Ahjussi?

21
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:05,220
We searched everywhere, but he's nowhere nearby.

22
00:02:05,220 --> 00:02:07,080
The police say that since he's an adult,

23
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:09,920
we can only file a missing-persons
report after 24 hours.

24
00:02:09,920 --> 00:02:13,900
Unni, what if we can't find my dad?

25
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:15,550
What if we never find him?

26
00:02:15,550 --> 00:02:16,770
It'll be all right.

27
00:02:16,770 --> 00:02:18,390
I'm the crazy one.

28
00:02:18,390 --> 00:02:21,840
Why was I so desperate to make a few extra bucks?

29
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:23,900
I left a patient with just a kid.

30
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:27,380
Gosh, I should've just told them
to screw it and stayed home.

31
00:02:27,380 --> 00:02:29,810
I should've been glued to his side.

32
00:02:29,810 --> 00:02:31,440
Don't worry, Ahjumma.

33
00:02:31,440 --> 00:02:32,850
Ahjussi will be back soon.

34
00:02:32,850 --> 00:02:36,040
Yes. He will, right? He'll come back, right?

35
00:02:36,040 --> 00:02:39,250
He wouldn't have dark thoughts, right?

36
00:02:39,250 --> 00:02:41,590
Of course not. No way, Ahjumma.

37
00:02:41,590 --> 00:02:44,000
That won't happen. Absolutely not.

38
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,950
For now, let's go inside and wait.

39
00:02:45,950 --> 00:02:48,220
Se Ri, you, too. Let's go.

40
00:03:26,150 --> 00:03:30,230
[Episode 10: Close to You]

41
00:03:30,930 --> 00:03:33,420
[Yeong Sik's Baekban]

42
00:03:39,100 --> 00:03:45,600
[Closed this evening due
to personal reasons. - Owner]

43
00:03:50,550 --> 00:03:55,000
Even so, do we really have
to shut the whole place?

44
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:58,350
I'll deliver these lunchboxes and be back.

45
00:03:58,350 --> 00:04:00,840
You should keep the store open.

46
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:03,410
Dinner is our main rush.

47
00:04:03,410 --> 00:04:06,270
Gosh, it's okay. Forget it.

48
00:04:07,630 --> 00:04:11,340
People come before money.
Not the other way around.

49
00:04:11,340 --> 00:04:13,150
I need to go.

50
00:04:14,180 --> 00:04:16,060
That woman, Man Ok...

51
00:04:16,060 --> 00:04:19,230
She's probably pacing on an empty stomach.

52
00:04:19,230 --> 00:04:21,170
Someone has to go feed her.

53
00:04:21,170 --> 00:04:23,720
Even if I have to force it down her throat.

54
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:25,470
And take care of Se Ri, too.

55
00:04:25,470 --> 00:04:28,090
Honestly, you're...

56
00:04:28,090 --> 00:04:29,380
Why? What?

57
00:04:29,380 --> 00:04:34,440
You were just saying earlier that
you live alone and die alone.

58
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:37,550
You're not related to Man Ok.

59
00:04:37,550 --> 00:04:41,040
It's not like she's your blood sister or anything.

60
00:04:43,190 --> 00:04:44,820
A friend.

61
00:04:45,490 --> 00:04:46,550
Huh?

62
00:04:46,550 --> 00:04:49,110
She and I are friends.

63
00:04:49,110 --> 00:04:51,830
So, I should go and comfort her.

64
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:56,730
I'll go with you, Mom.

65
00:04:57,650 --> 00:05:00,540
Se Ri is my friend, too.

66
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:13,330
Seo Jong Hui.

67
00:05:16,270 --> 00:05:17,960
What are you doing here out of the blue?

68
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:19,690
Just because.

69
00:05:21,090 --> 00:05:24,760
Do you have a little time to hang out with me?

70
00:05:41,510 --> 00:05:44,440
Shouldn't you be playing baseball,
not horseback riding?

71
00:05:46,630 --> 00:05:48,080
You're so good at hitting.

72
00:05:48,080 --> 00:05:52,670
I came here and did this
whenever I was stressed out.

73
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:05,300
How refreshing.

74
00:06:07,630 --> 00:06:11,850
You say that, but your face doesn't
look refreshed at all.

75
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:15,020
Whoa, psychic.

76
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:18,810
I've always wondered.

77
00:06:18,810 --> 00:06:22,210
How do you read me so well?

78
00:06:23,020 --> 00:06:25,410
Sometimes, it's a little scary.

79
00:06:25,410 --> 00:06:28,020
If you pay attention, you can see it.

80
00:06:28,990 --> 00:06:31,270
You were paying attention to me?

81
00:06:34,790 --> 00:06:37,430
Not that kind of attention.

82
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:44,220
Oppa.

83
00:06:45,330 --> 00:06:49,590
Seven years must've been
a longer time than I thought.

84
00:06:50,990 --> 00:06:53,240
You know that feeling?

85
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:56,740
Everyone is already way up ahead,

86
00:06:56,740 --> 00:06:59,300
and I'm the only one
who can't take the first step.

87
00:06:59,300 --> 00:07:02,610
Like I'm circling the edge of the starting line.

88
00:07:03,730 --> 00:07:06,030
I want to join in.

89
00:07:07,380 --> 00:07:09,830
I want to go with them,

90
00:07:11,490 --> 00:07:14,550
but I don't know how to catch up.

91
00:07:17,300 --> 00:07:21,650
Gosh. What the heck happened
in the past seven years?

92
00:07:21,650 --> 00:07:25,270
A lot can happen in seven years.

93
00:07:26,340 --> 00:07:28,690
It did for you, too, didn't it?

94
00:07:32,610 --> 00:07:34,730
I told you last time

95
00:07:35,910 --> 00:07:38,680
that you should be honest with your heart.

96
00:07:39,450 --> 00:07:44,520
Be honest about your feelings, but don't rush.

97
00:07:45,820 --> 00:07:49,240
Respect other people's feelings. And...

98
00:07:50,620 --> 00:07:53,100
accept things as they are.

99
00:07:54,650 --> 00:07:56,360
As they are?

100
00:08:05,190 --> 00:08:08,120
If Yeong Rye and I fight,

101
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:11,140
you'll naturally take Yeong Rye's side, right?

102
00:08:11,140 --> 00:08:13,240
Since that's the natural course?

103
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:15,690
Right.

104
00:08:18,970 --> 00:08:21,590
But I hope you don't fight.

105
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:25,580
Because I want to take your side, too.

106
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:28,700
You're just saying that.

107
00:08:32,850 --> 00:08:35,960
Hearing what you said gives me a little strength.

108
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:37,860
It's comforting, too.

109
00:08:41,460 --> 00:08:44,140
I'll just have to do what I can.

110
00:08:47,590 --> 00:08:49,360
Let's go now.

111
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:52,090
I've taken up too much of your time.

112
00:09:04,060 --> 00:09:08,560
Yeong Bae, bring Se Ri out, so she can eat.

113
00:09:08,560 --> 00:09:10,780
Okay. Just a moment.

114
00:09:11,970 --> 00:09:13,750
Let's go eat.

115
00:09:13,750 --> 00:09:15,340
Okay?

116
00:09:15,340 --> 00:09:16,750
Se Ri.

117
00:09:16,750 --> 00:09:18,870
I don't want to eat.

118
00:09:18,870 --> 00:09:21,820
I was snappy with him.

119
00:09:21,820 --> 00:09:24,060
That he was discharged for no reason

120
00:09:24,060 --> 00:09:27,050
and I can't even go to your house.

121
00:09:27,050 --> 00:09:30,750
I made a whole scene and acted out.

122
00:09:41,070 --> 00:09:46,030
Yeong Mi has been listening to this
song called "Don't Worry, Be Happy."

123
00:09:46,030 --> 00:09:48,450
What's that mean?

124
00:09:48,450 --> 00:09:57,030
You're not teasing me because I got
32 points on my English midterm, are you?

125
00:09:57,030 --> 00:10:00,510
It means, don't worry and be happy.

126
00:10:00,510 --> 00:10:03,150
Don't worry, be happy.

127
00:10:03,150 --> 00:10:06,690
Don't worry, be happy.

128
00:10:07,530 --> 00:10:10,130
Everybody hurts sometimes.

129
00:10:10,130 --> 00:10:14,500
But just worrying? That only
makes it twice as big.

130
00:10:14,500 --> 00:10:18,650
So, don't worry, be happy.

131
00:10:18,650 --> 00:10:21,430
It will soon pass, whatever it is.

132
00:10:21,430 --> 00:10:24,300
Don't worry and choose to be happy.

133
00:10:24,300 --> 00:10:27,380
Whatever it may be, it'll pass.

134
00:10:27,380 --> 00:10:29,240
That's what it means.

135
00:10:31,700 --> 00:10:36,210
Your dad is going to be okay.

136
00:10:37,190 --> 00:10:40,150
Gosh, I'm so annoyed.

137
00:10:40,150 --> 00:10:45,480
How can you be so cool at
a time like this, Ko Yeong Bae?

138
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:58,200
Even if your heart is all shaken up to pieces,

139
00:10:58,200 --> 00:11:01,000
you have to eat something.

140
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:04,950
So, you can keep searching and
handle what comes after.

141
00:11:04,950 --> 00:11:06,840
Just take a bite.

142
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:13,960
I seasoned it lightly so it'll
go down easy. Come on.

143
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:15,130
Here.

144
00:11:15,130 --> 00:11:18,140
Unni, thank you,

145
00:11:18,140 --> 00:11:23,350
but I don't think I can swallow
any food right now.

146
00:11:25,010 --> 00:11:28,990
Sure, I know that feeling.

147
00:11:28,990 --> 00:11:30,600
Even when starving, you crave the familiar broth.

148
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:33,770
Even when you're old, you still want your hubby.

149
00:11:33,770 --> 00:11:38,170
I felt the same way when Yeong Sik's
father was sick in bed.

150
00:11:38,170 --> 00:11:40,280
Even after all the fighting,

151
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:43,530
there's a moment you feel sorry and feel for him.

152
00:11:43,530 --> 00:11:46,420
Unni, he'll be okay, right?

153
00:11:46,420 --> 00:11:50,320
He's not lying somewhere out on the street, is he?

154
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:52,310
You said he took his wallet.

155
00:11:52,310 --> 00:11:54,000
His ID is in it.

156
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:57,200
If he had collapsed, we would've heard about it.

157
00:11:57,200 --> 00:12:00,190
That's right. We'd have heard something.

158
00:12:01,640 --> 00:12:05,220
Gosh, I'm getting upset again.

159
00:12:05,220 --> 00:12:07,380
He should know better.

160
00:12:07,380 --> 00:12:10,010
Why is he making his family worry like this?

161
00:12:10,010 --> 00:12:13,720
Why on earth did he leave the
house in that condition?

162
00:12:15,030 --> 00:12:17,040
We had a fight.

163
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:18,520
What?

164
00:12:18,520 --> 00:12:21,950
I talked back to my father.

165
00:12:22,820 --> 00:12:25,150
I just couldn't understand.

166
00:12:25,150 --> 00:12:27,680
Why is he so stubborn all the time?

167
00:12:27,680 --> 00:12:31,880
I told him he couldn't leave
the hospital yet, but he still...

168
00:12:33,730 --> 00:12:35,510
Jae Pil.

169
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:44,340
Jae Pil, about his discharge...

170
00:12:46,290 --> 00:12:49,600
I think he did that for your sake.

171
00:12:50,550 --> 00:12:52,430
What?

172
00:12:52,430 --> 00:12:54,960
He told me yesterday.

173
00:12:55,870 --> 00:13:00,900
He felt his difficult personality
was making things hard for you.

174
00:13:00,900 --> 00:13:04,690
And that must be embarrassing
for you at the hospital.

175
00:13:06,750 --> 00:13:12,520
I think he overheard what people were saying.

176
00:13:18,700 --> 00:13:20,890
Why listen to that...

177
00:13:22,070 --> 00:13:23,500
Why care about that?

178
00:13:23,500 --> 00:13:27,520
Since when did he ever care about me? Shit...

179
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:30,670
Don't say that, Jae Pil.

180
00:13:30,670 --> 00:13:35,480
Your father cares about you a lot.

181
00:13:37,730 --> 00:13:42,060
He told me not to say anything,
so I kept my mouth shut.

182
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:46,600
Your mom's death wasn't his fault.

183
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:50,010
Your father truly loved her.

184
00:13:50,010 --> 00:13:53,310
I know. I worked as his secretary at the time.

185
00:13:54,420 --> 00:13:58,650
Your mother's circumstances
drove her to marry without love.

186
00:13:58,650 --> 00:14:01,580
She couldn't open her heart to your father.

187
00:14:01,580 --> 00:14:05,860
That's how she fell deeper into
alcoholism and depression.

188
00:14:05,860 --> 00:14:09,490
The doctor said she'd die
if he left her like that.

189
00:14:09,490 --> 00:14:13,260
Your father was trying to save your mother,
even if it meant being forceful.

190
00:14:13,260 --> 00:14:15,130
Wait a minute.

191
00:14:16,040 --> 00:14:22,950
By chance, could Ahjussi have gone there?

192
00:15:16,550 --> 00:15:18,340
I'm here.

193
00:15:20,900 --> 00:15:23,690
It's been too long, hasn't it?

194
00:15:25,940 --> 00:15:28,160
I wanted to come sooner,

195
00:15:29,140 --> 00:15:30,820
but my condition...

196
00:15:32,330 --> 00:15:34,210
isn't so great.

197
00:15:35,370 --> 00:15:36,870
Honey...

198
00:15:38,420 --> 00:15:43,950
I brought your favorite liquor and tangerines.

199
00:16:06,030 --> 00:16:08,870
I couldn't understand you,

200
00:16:08,870 --> 00:16:11,030
but as I live,

201
00:16:12,190 --> 00:16:14,830
I get it a little now.

202
00:16:18,950 --> 00:16:26,280
How torturous it is
when your heart feels like hell.

203
00:16:31,070 --> 00:16:34,670
After the department store went down,

204
00:16:34,670 --> 00:16:37,940
I became a burden to my kids.

205
00:16:37,940 --> 00:16:42,420
I, Han Gi Bok, am nothing without my pride.

206
00:16:45,460 --> 00:16:48,310
It's hell, Eun Hye.

207
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:58,830
After leaving me like that,

208
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:04,320
are you happy there?

209
00:17:05,430 --> 00:17:07,300
Father!

210
00:17:15,390 --> 00:17:18,830
What are you doing here?

211
00:17:18,830 --> 00:17:21,030
How did you know I was here?

212
00:17:21,030 --> 00:17:25,670
If you wanted to come here, you should've
told me! Why do you always…

213
00:17:27,920 --> 00:17:30,060
I'm sorry.

214
00:17:30,060 --> 00:17:32,930
I didn't mean to make you worry.

215
00:17:34,300 --> 00:17:36,940
I just really wanted to come.

216
00:17:42,410 --> 00:17:44,060
I'm sorry.

217
00:17:49,820 --> 00:17:51,930
I'm sorry, Father.

218
00:17:53,980 --> 00:17:57,800
I was so young and foolish.

219
00:17:57,800 --> 00:18:00,820
For over ten years, I misunderstood you

220
00:18:00,820 --> 00:18:04,460
and resented you. I made you so lonely.

221
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:07,760
I'm sorry.

222
00:18:14,940 --> 00:18:17,730
Why didn't you tell me?

223
00:18:18,940 --> 00:18:23,200
Why did you let me hate you? Why? Why...

224
00:18:30,760 --> 00:18:32,480
I'm sorry.

225
00:18:36,150 --> 00:18:37,820
Sorry.

226
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:15,490
[Yeonseo University Hospital]

227
00:19:19,870 --> 00:19:21,970
Doctor Han! I'll enjoy this.

228
00:19:21,970 --> 00:19:25,090
It's so good. Thank you.

229
00:19:25,090 --> 00:19:26,660
I'll have one more.

230
00:19:30,390 --> 00:19:32,310
How can you work without eating?

231
00:19:32,310 --> 00:19:34,120
After I do this.

232
00:19:34,830 --> 00:19:38,500
Hey, Jae Pil! The star is finally here.
Come sit here.

233
00:19:38,500 --> 00:19:39,760
You're here.

234
00:19:39,760 --> 00:19:41,380
Jong Hui.

235
00:19:41,380 --> 00:19:43,960
There's this sandwich shop I often go to.

236
00:19:43,960 --> 00:19:46,060
They're really good.

237
00:19:46,060 --> 00:19:49,550
They treated me so well when I was hospitalized.

238
00:19:49,550 --> 00:19:53,440
This is a thank-you and a little bribe
to take good care of you.

239
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:54,810
Sit down.

240
00:19:55,530 --> 00:19:56,730
Hey, you!

241
00:19:57,430 --> 00:19:59,390
You sneaky boy.

242
00:19:59,390 --> 00:20:03,740
You had a pretty girlfriend all this time,
yet you acted like you didn't.

243
00:20:03,740 --> 00:20:04,880
Bad boy!

244
00:20:04,880 --> 00:20:06,540
That's unacceptable, man.

245
00:20:06,540 --> 00:20:08,270
She's not my girlfriend.

246
00:20:08,270 --> 00:20:10,210
It's not like that, man.

247
00:20:10,210 --> 00:20:12,630
But it's not like I'm not. Am I right?

248
00:20:12,630 --> 00:20:17,340
I'm not your boyfriend. Am I wrong?

249
00:20:17,340 --> 00:20:19,360
She's right. She has a point.

250
00:20:19,360 --> 00:20:21,530
You're pretty and funny, too?

251
00:20:21,530 --> 00:20:23,350
Man, you lucky bastard.

252
00:20:23,350 --> 00:20:26,370
Hey. When will I get a girlfriend like her?

253
00:20:26,370 --> 00:20:31,120
The way I see it, Jae Pil must've
saved our country in his past life.

254
00:20:31,120 --> 00:20:32,960
And I probably betrayed it.

255
00:20:33,930 --> 00:20:35,360
Please dig in.

256
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:36,760
You have one, too.

257
00:20:36,760 --> 00:20:39,000
It's really good. Try it.

258
00:20:41,210 --> 00:20:42,650
[Daeyang Group]

259
00:20:42,650 --> 00:20:44,970
So, did you look into it?

260
00:20:44,970 --> 00:20:48,070
Yes. Her friend's name is Ko Yeong Rye.

261
00:20:48,070 --> 00:20:49,640
They're the same age

262
00:20:49,640 --> 00:20:52,570
and they were closest when they
worked at Cheongah Transportation.

263
00:20:52,570 --> 00:20:56,350
Her mother currently runs
a restaurant in Yeongeun Market.

264
00:20:58,260 --> 00:20:59,860
And...

265
00:21:01,780 --> 00:21:03,380
And?

266
00:21:03,380 --> 00:21:07,400
Ko Yeong Rye is currently employed
at Jullee Beauty Salon.

267
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:09,180
What? Jullee Beauty Salon?

268
00:21:09,180 --> 00:21:10,600
Yes.

269
00:21:20,570 --> 00:21:23,890
Her nose job hasn't settled yet.

270
00:21:23,890 --> 00:21:26,210
- I agree.
- She's out.

271
00:21:27,210 --> 00:21:32,020
You're saying Cheongdam Salon
intercepted her, right?

272
00:21:32,020 --> 00:21:34,030
I-Interc-

273
00:21:35,850 --> 00:21:39,120
Seriously, no loss there.

274
00:21:44,130 --> 00:21:48,840
Why is her face so tacky? Seriously!

275
00:21:48,840 --> 00:21:51,360
Any news from Michelle's side?

276
00:21:51,360 --> 00:21:54,710
They've probably picked their
candidate and started warming up.

277
00:21:54,710 --> 00:21:56,370
Not yet.

278
00:21:57,220 --> 00:22:00,900
Michelle's director keeps
everyone on a tight leash.

279
00:22:00,900 --> 00:22:04,150
Right. That ahjumma is no pushover.

280
00:22:04,150 --> 00:22:06,880
She's probably also conscious of us.

281
00:22:09,060 --> 00:22:13,940
You still haven't made up with her, right?

282
00:22:15,280 --> 00:22:17,380
There's that misunderstanding between you two.

283
00:22:17,380 --> 00:22:19,230
Misunderstanding, my foot.

284
00:22:19,230 --> 00:22:21,770
I did betray her.

285
00:22:21,770 --> 00:22:26,100
No. Calling it betrayal sounds so tacky.

286
00:22:26,100 --> 00:22:29,210
I went independent based on my abilities.

287
00:22:30,160 --> 00:22:32,700
Why can't we find a face that stands out?

288
00:22:32,700 --> 00:22:34,730
- This is driving me crazy.
- Wait, wait, wait...

289
00:22:34,730 --> 00:22:36,470
- No, she's-
- Ma'am?

290
00:22:36,470 --> 00:22:38,460
Oh, my! Chairwoman! Oh, my!

291
00:22:38,460 --> 00:22:41,850
Oh, my gosh. Chairwoman! Oh, my gosh!

292
00:22:41,850 --> 00:22:44,830
Chairwoman, what brings you here
without an appointment?

293
00:22:44,830 --> 00:22:46,940
Something suddenly came up.

294
00:22:46,940 --> 00:22:48,230
You can do an updo, right?

295
00:22:48,230 --> 00:22:54,160
Of course. We're always ready for you.
365 days a year, day or night.

296
00:22:54,160 --> 00:22:55,800
Come this way. I'll take care of you.

297
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:58,260
No, today...

298
00:22:58,260 --> 00:23:00,830
I'd actually like her to do it for me.

299
00:23:00,830 --> 00:23:05,630
My daughter seems to like the way
she does her hair, and I'm curious myself.

300
00:23:07,270 --> 00:23:08,890
Ms. Ko?

301
00:23:11,290 --> 00:23:12,710
Yes.

302
00:23:35,740 --> 00:23:37,590
Excuse me.

303
00:23:37,590 --> 00:23:40,030
Give this side as much volume as possible.

304
00:23:40,030 --> 00:23:42,430
Yes. I understand.

305
00:23:53,320 --> 00:23:54,700
This side- Ouch!

306
00:23:54,700 --> 00:23:57,850
Oh! A-Are you all right? Oh, no...

307
00:23:57,850 --> 00:24:01,160
Oh, my! Chairwoman! Oh, my gosh!

308
00:24:01,160 --> 00:24:03,570
Unni, get some cold water.

309
00:24:03,570 --> 00:24:06,260
- Oh, dear, it looks like you got burned.
- Please...

310
00:24:06,260 --> 00:24:07,800
Ms. Ko!

311
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:11,970
What should we do? Chairwoman. Oh, no.

312
00:24:22,310 --> 00:24:25,110
Chairwoman, are you okay?

313
00:24:25,110 --> 00:24:28,080
Oh, no, that must sting so badly.

314
00:24:28,080 --> 00:24:30,770
We rarely make mistakes like this,

315
00:24:30,770 --> 00:24:34,560
but as the owner, I'll compensate,
and I ask for your forgiveness.

316
00:24:34,560 --> 00:24:37,790
I'm truly sorry, Chairwoman.

317
00:24:37,790 --> 00:24:40,680
Forget the compensation.
It's not worth much, anyway.

318
00:24:40,680 --> 00:24:42,370
But more than that,

319
00:24:44,030 --> 00:24:47,020
would a customer want to return to a salon

320
00:24:47,020 --> 00:24:49,950
with an incompetent hairstylist
who lacks basic skills?

321
00:24:49,950 --> 00:24:51,320
Pardon?

322
00:24:56,630 --> 00:24:58,290
I'm very sorry, Chairwoman.

323
00:24:58,290 --> 00:25:01,170
It was a serious mistake on my part.

324
00:25:01,170 --> 00:25:04,640
But before using a curling iron,

325
00:25:04,640 --> 00:25:07,560
I always give a warning, like I did earlier.

326
00:25:07,560 --> 00:25:11,800
If they need to move, let me know.
It could cause a burn.

327
00:25:11,800 --> 00:25:15,060
- But in the earlier situation-
- So, I didn't tell you in advance?

328
00:25:15,060 --> 00:25:17,360
So, it was all my fault?

329
00:25:17,360 --> 00:25:19,530
No, that's not what I meant.

330
00:25:19,530 --> 00:25:23,480
A mere staff member is trying to lecture me?

331
00:25:25,080 --> 00:25:28,070
I'm so offended that I can't keep
coming to Jullee anymore.

332
00:25:28,070 --> 00:25:30,410
I'll have to find another salon.

333
00:25:30,410 --> 00:25:34,880
Chairwoman, if you leave like this...

334
00:25:40,960 --> 00:25:44,240
You dare talk back about warnings
when you should be

335
00:25:44,240 --> 00:25:47,230
on your knees begging forgiveness?

336
00:25:47,230 --> 00:25:48,760
You're fired.

337
00:25:48,760 --> 00:25:52,580
Pack your things and get out. Got it?

338
00:25:52,580 --> 00:25:54,460
Chairwoman.

339
00:25:54,460 --> 00:25:56,370
Chairwoman!

340
00:26:13,410 --> 00:26:15,790
Hey, Jae Pil.

341
00:26:15,790 --> 00:26:17,860
You know your other girlfriend?

342
00:26:17,860 --> 00:26:19,640
The one I asked you to introduce me to?

343
00:26:19,640 --> 00:26:21,950
Yeong Rye? What about her?

344
00:26:21,950 --> 00:26:25,340
I just saw her getting fired by her boss.

345
00:26:26,200 --> 00:26:28,720
She burned a customer or something.

346
00:26:28,720 --> 00:26:32,650
It didn't look that bad. Must've
been someone important.

347
00:26:33,680 --> 00:26:35,820
Really?

348
00:26:35,820 --> 00:26:37,950
Are you sure she was fired?

349
00:27:00,150 --> 00:27:01,820
What are you doing out here?

350
00:27:01,820 --> 00:27:04,260
I came to try that dye job you recommended.

351
00:27:04,260 --> 00:27:06,970
You came on a wrong day.

352
00:27:06,970 --> 00:27:10,510
I just got fired.

353
00:27:10,510 --> 00:27:14,690
- What?
- But I don't know where I should go.

354
00:27:14,690 --> 00:27:18,230
If I go home now, Mom is
going to be really worried.

355
00:28:06,820 --> 00:28:10,420
So, you liked modern pop.

356
00:28:10,420 --> 00:28:12,110
I didn't know.

357
00:28:12,110 --> 00:28:13,800
Should I play this?

358
00:28:13,800 --> 00:28:15,770
Let's just go quietly.

359
00:28:16,720 --> 00:28:19,060
You're not in the mood for music.

360
00:28:20,060 --> 00:28:24,540
I could fool a ghost, but not you.

361
00:28:27,510 --> 00:28:30,890
But why aren't you asking?
How I ended up getting fired.

362
00:28:30,890 --> 00:28:32,180
What's there to ask?

363
00:28:32,180 --> 00:28:35,090
I'm sure you didn't screw up
big time to get canned.

364
00:28:35,090 --> 00:28:37,430
Must've been an unfair firing, right?

365
00:28:37,430 --> 00:28:39,120
No.

366
00:28:40,010 --> 00:28:43,550
It's not like I did nothing wrong,

367
00:28:43,550 --> 00:28:46,110
so I wouldn't call it an unfair dismissal.

368
00:28:46,110 --> 00:28:47,890
What are you, a saint?

369
00:28:47,890 --> 00:28:50,200
You'll get sick if you do that.

370
00:28:51,710 --> 00:28:56,820
Well, how about using this chance
to rest and focus on studying?

371
00:28:56,820 --> 00:28:59,840
You said you're aiming for college
entrance this year anyway.

372
00:28:59,840 --> 00:29:03,370
But I still have to work, too.

373
00:29:03,370 --> 00:29:06,690
The landlord keeps trying to raise
Mom's restaurant rent,

374
00:29:06,690 --> 00:29:10,600
and I need to chip in for living expenses.

375
00:29:10,600 --> 00:29:14,510
At least until Oppa becomes
a judge and has a steady income.

376
00:29:22,980 --> 00:29:26,210
I know a job that's perfect
for a solid talent like you.

377
00:29:26,210 --> 00:29:29,040
Want to go check it out?

378
00:29:31,750 --> 00:29:36,570
Whoa, is this really your office?

379
00:29:36,570 --> 00:29:37,770
Yeah.

380
00:29:37,770 --> 00:29:39,820
It's amazing.

381
00:29:40,730 --> 00:29:44,800
I start work next week, but I haven't
picked a secretary yet.

382
00:29:44,800 --> 00:29:49,620
The secretary my mom recommended would
be my parents' eyes, ears, and speaker.

383
00:29:50,530 --> 00:29:54,270
So? Want to be my secretary?

384
00:29:54,270 --> 00:29:55,950
There won't be much to do.

385
00:29:55,950 --> 00:29:58,540
Manage my schedule and communicate with me.

386
00:29:58,540 --> 00:30:02,830
And I'll pretend not to notice
if you study the rest of your time.

387
00:30:04,310 --> 00:30:06,730
It's such a tempting offer.

388
00:30:06,730 --> 00:30:10,710
This isn't even a multiple-choice
question, but a yes or no.

389
00:30:12,210 --> 00:30:17,250
But if I also accept this, I'd feel shameless.

390
00:30:17,250 --> 00:30:20,140
I've already received so much from you.

391
00:30:21,120 --> 00:30:24,080
Can't you take a little more while you're at it?

392
00:30:24,080 --> 00:30:27,200
- You can pay me back all at once later.
- My gosh.

393
00:30:27,200 --> 00:30:30,700
I can't accept something
I might not be able to repay.

394
00:30:30,700 --> 00:30:35,050
I'll try to get through this on my own somehow.

395
00:30:36,180 --> 00:30:40,420
But I'm really grateful, and I feel so supported.

396
00:30:40,420 --> 00:30:43,270
You're my Daddy-Long-Legs, as always.

397
00:30:47,900 --> 00:30:52,340
I'm starting to dislike being
just your Daddy-Long-Legs.

398
00:30:52,340 --> 00:30:54,220
What?

399
00:30:54,220 --> 00:30:55,810
Never mind.

400
00:30:56,820 --> 00:30:58,430
I think I was too hasty.

401
00:30:58,430 --> 00:31:01,360
Okay, let's pretend I never made that offer.

402
00:31:01,360 --> 00:31:05,300
Instead, let me buy you dinner today,
as consolation.

403
00:31:05,300 --> 00:31:09,800
- To celebrate your unemployment.
- I'll accept that offer.

404
00:31:09,800 --> 00:31:12,170
- Buy me something tasty, Oppa.
- Sure.

405
00:31:12,170 --> 00:31:13,670
Let's go.

406
00:31:17,180 --> 00:31:19,520
What the hell? Let's go for it.

407
00:31:19,520 --> 00:31:21,490
I've got nothing to be afraid of.

408
00:31:21,490 --> 00:31:24,700
I have to get my hands dirty to get the work done.

409
00:31:24,700 --> 00:31:27,590
I just have to take care of it
before it gets worse.

410
00:31:27,590 --> 00:31:29,710
Geez...

411
00:31:29,710 --> 00:31:32,810
I'll be a man about it and grab him by the collar.

412
00:31:32,810 --> 00:31:34,500
"How long have you been seeing Jeong Bun?

413
00:31:34,500 --> 00:31:38,690
Are you thinking of marriage? No? Then, back off!"

414
00:31:38,690 --> 00:31:40,810
If he says he is,

415
00:31:40,810 --> 00:31:42,500
then, I'll say...

416
00:31:42,500 --> 00:31:46,600
"Let's play fair.
I used to be pretty close to her."

417
00:32:20,790 --> 00:32:23,360
What the heck? W-Why am I...

418
00:32:42,580 --> 00:32:46,190
You're tough, as expected, Ko Yeong Rye.

419
00:32:46,190 --> 00:32:48,040
- Huh?
- Nothing.

420
00:32:48,040 --> 00:32:51,490
You're eating so well for someone
who just lost her job.

421
00:32:53,570 --> 00:32:57,720
Actually, I was starving all day.

422
00:32:57,720 --> 00:33:01,700
I woke up late and didn't get to eat breakfast.

423
00:33:04,870 --> 00:33:06,070
Eat up.

424
00:33:06,070 --> 00:33:08,090
You'll need energy to find another job.

425
00:33:08,090 --> 00:33:11,610
I'm not hungry enough to steal your food.

426
00:33:13,340 --> 00:33:18,200
But given the kind
of day it's been, I'll eat plenty.

427
00:33:22,410 --> 00:33:28,490
Oppa, I think you'd make a great
husband when you get married.

428
00:33:28,490 --> 00:33:31,080
You're so attentive and considerate.

429
00:33:31,080 --> 00:33:32,820
Do you really think so?

430
00:33:32,820 --> 00:33:34,800
Yeah! Of course.

431
00:33:34,800 --> 00:33:39,830
I don't know who, but the woman
who marries you will hit the jackpot.

432
00:33:40,980 --> 00:33:43,180
If you think I'm so great,

433
00:33:43,180 --> 00:33:45,920
you should grab that jackpot.

434
00:33:48,370 --> 00:33:52,040
Come on. That would be too shameless of me.

435
00:33:52,040 --> 00:33:54,300
I wouldn't dream of it.

436
00:33:54,300 --> 00:33:57,220
I'd be punished.

437
00:33:57,220 --> 00:33:59,760
My son! Hyeon!

438
00:34:01,090 --> 00:34:02,610
Mom.

439
00:34:03,920 --> 00:34:06,130
You're having a late lunch.

440
00:34:06,860 --> 00:34:10,470
But who is this lady? Your girlfriend?

441
00:34:15,300 --> 00:34:18,050
My name is Ko Yeong Rye.

442
00:34:18,050 --> 00:34:21,840
I'm the sister of his friend, Ko Yeong Sik.

443
00:34:21,840 --> 00:34:23,970
Yeong Sik?

444
00:34:23,970 --> 00:34:25,640
You're Yeong Sik's sister?

445
00:34:25,640 --> 00:34:27,490
Yes.

446
00:34:27,490 --> 00:34:29,620
I like this woman.

447
00:34:32,330 --> 00:34:34,500
I like her.

448
00:34:35,660 --> 00:34:37,720
Although it's one-sided for now.

449
00:34:57,270 --> 00:35:00,420
Now that I've said it, I'm embarrassed.

450
00:35:00,420 --> 00:35:01,860
Surprised, huh?

451
00:35:01,860 --> 00:35:03,840
A little.

452
00:35:04,650 --> 00:35:08,740
I was going to keep you close and
wait for the right moment to confess.

453
00:35:08,740 --> 00:35:11,050
But because of Mom...

454
00:35:14,800 --> 00:35:17,480
- Oppa, I-
- Wait.

455
00:35:18,280 --> 00:35:20,460
Don't speak so hastily.

456
00:35:20,460 --> 00:35:23,080
I'm not asking for an answer right now.

457
00:35:23,080 --> 00:35:27,180
I didn't want to introduce you
to my mom as just my friend's sister.

458
00:35:27,180 --> 00:35:28,450
Take your time.

459
00:35:28,450 --> 00:35:31,230
Don't just think of me as your Daddy-Long-Legs.

460
00:35:32,110 --> 00:35:35,840
Consider me as a man from all angles.

461
00:35:35,840 --> 00:35:39,250
And then give me your answer.

462
00:35:39,250 --> 00:35:41,700
You can do that much for me, right?

463
00:35:43,850 --> 00:35:46,820
Considering my devotion up until now.

464
00:35:49,590 --> 00:35:51,480
Wait at the entrance. I'll bring my car.

465
00:35:51,480 --> 00:35:53,060
It's fine.

466
00:35:54,350 --> 00:35:56,470
I'll take the bus.

467
00:35:57,320 --> 00:36:00,460
I think that will be better today.

468
00:36:19,880 --> 00:36:23,090
Do you avoid crap because you're scared?
No, because it's filthy.

469
00:36:28,080 --> 00:36:32,890
Where's the Jjakgoong bar I like?

470
00:36:34,250 --> 00:36:35,930
Here it is.

471
00:36:38,500 --> 00:36:40,430
Kiddo!

472
00:36:40,430 --> 00:36:41,900
You're Jeong Bun's daughter, right?

473
00:36:41,900 --> 00:36:44,640
I'm not "Kiddo." I'm Su Jin.

474
00:36:44,640 --> 00:36:48,140
Right, Su Jin. You like Jjakgoong bars, too?

475
00:36:48,970 --> 00:36:53,750
What should we do? There's only one
Jjakgoong bar left.

476
00:36:53,750 --> 00:36:57,200
But I happened to grab it first.

477
00:36:59,990 --> 00:37:01,850
You want it that bad?

478
00:37:02,650 --> 00:37:05,880
Wow. It's not easy to split this exactly in half.

479
00:37:05,880 --> 00:37:07,320
You've got skills, Su Jin.

480
00:37:07,320 --> 00:37:09,690
I eat it every day with Mom.

481
00:37:09,690 --> 00:37:11,160
With your mom?

482
00:37:11,160 --> 00:37:14,140
Jeong Bun likes Jjakgoong bars?

483
00:37:14,140 --> 00:37:16,430
Goodness.

484
00:37:16,430 --> 00:37:18,540
Father and daughter are the spitting image.

485
00:37:18,540 --> 00:37:20,910
You look exactly alike.

486
00:37:24,100 --> 00:37:26,870
She said you and I look exactly the same.

487
00:37:27,940 --> 00:37:30,020
That's funny, huh?

488
00:37:32,390 --> 00:37:36,350
By the way, how old are you?
Do you go to kindergarten?

489
00:37:36,350 --> 00:37:39,920
I'm seven years old.
Sunny Kindergarten, Apple class.

490
00:37:39,920 --> 00:37:43,050
Seven years old. Sunny Kindergarten.

491
00:37:44,830 --> 00:37:46,330
Seven...

492
00:37:48,880 --> 00:37:51,130
Seven years old?

493
00:37:51,130 --> 00:37:54,210
When's your birthday?

494
00:37:54,940 --> 00:37:56,840
July 30th.

495
00:37:56,840 --> 00:38:00,450
On my birthday, Mom and I
go to Children's Grand Park.

496
00:38:02,060 --> 00:38:03,600
July?

497
00:38:04,620 --> 00:38:08,280
July? October, November, December...

498
00:38:24,820 --> 00:38:27,230
Damn. What is it now?

499
00:38:27,230 --> 00:38:28,850
Why do you keep lurking around?

500
00:38:28,850 --> 00:38:30,020
Let me check one thing.

501
00:38:30,020 --> 00:38:33,460
What's there to check between us?

502
00:38:34,280 --> 00:38:36,020
Su Jin...

503
00:38:37,210 --> 00:38:39,650
Who's her father?

504
00:38:39,650 --> 00:38:43,400
Is she my daughter by any chance?

505
00:38:43,970 --> 00:38:45,490
Goodness.

506
00:38:45,490 --> 00:38:49,900
What kind of nonsense are you spouting?

507
00:38:49,900 --> 00:38:52,630
Even a stray mutt would laugh.

508
00:38:52,630 --> 00:38:56,580
I can't believe the garbage I'm hearing at my age.

509
00:38:56,580 --> 00:38:59,910
Don't go running that big mouth.

510
00:38:59,910 --> 00:39:04,110
Keep it up, and I'll nail it shut, you hear?

511
00:39:04,110 --> 00:39:06,340
So, she's not?

512
00:39:06,340 --> 00:39:08,050
Are you sure?

513
00:39:11,550 --> 00:39:14,160
Look me in the eyes and say it.

514
00:39:14,160 --> 00:39:16,590
I've done the math.

515
00:39:16,590 --> 00:39:20,800
If Su Jin is seven and was born in July,

516
00:39:20,800 --> 00:39:24,100
she was conceived when we were together.

517
00:39:24,100 --> 00:39:26,320
Were you seeing some other guy?

518
00:39:26,320 --> 00:39:29,300
Back then? You?

519
00:39:32,410 --> 00:39:35,960
No. You're not that type of person.

520
00:39:35,960 --> 00:39:37,400
Right?

521
00:39:38,160 --> 00:39:39,700
Tell me.

522
00:39:42,400 --> 00:39:46,700
Su Jin is my daughter, isn't she?

523
00:39:54,370 --> 00:39:55,860
Hey!

524
00:40:04,150 --> 00:40:06,170
Why are you here again?

525
00:40:07,220 --> 00:40:09,220
I told you not to come around.

526
00:40:09,220 --> 00:40:10,670
Stay out of this.

527
00:40:10,670 --> 00:40:13,830
This is about Jeong Bun, Su Jin, and me.

528
00:40:19,300 --> 00:40:22,720
I'm right, aren't I?

529
00:40:22,720 --> 00:40:24,370
Su Jin...

530
00:40:26,140 --> 00:40:28,310
is our daughter, right?

531
00:40:46,110 --> 00:40:49,200
Where have you been wandering around?

532
00:40:49,200 --> 00:40:51,000
Han Jae Pil!

533
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:53,440
My legs were about to fall off.

534
00:40:53,440 --> 00:40:55,260
You didn't even tell me...

535
00:40:55,260 --> 00:40:56,570
I was worried!

536
00:40:56,570 --> 00:40:58,600
What if you went to the Han River

537
00:40:58,600 --> 00:41:02,830
or passed out drunk
from the shock of getting fired? How-

538
00:41:04,510 --> 00:41:09,110
I couldn't relax unless I saw you
with my own eyes.

539
00:41:10,010 --> 00:41:11,690
You're laughing?

540
00:41:12,680 --> 00:41:13,970
Give me.

541
00:41:16,500 --> 00:41:19,960
You must be hungry. Want to go eat noodles?

542
00:41:20,930 --> 00:41:22,280
Are you okay?

543
00:41:22,280 --> 00:41:23,880
Let's go.

544
00:41:23,880 --> 00:41:25,370
It's on you.

545
00:41:26,530 --> 00:41:27,720
- Thank you.
- Enjoy.

546
00:41:27,720 --> 00:41:29,540
Thank you.

547
00:41:31,790 --> 00:41:39,280
♫ When darkness falls in my quiet heart ♫

548
00:41:40,210 --> 00:41:41,790
Good?

549
00:41:41,790 --> 00:41:46,100
♫ The sky outside is filled with stars ♫

550
00:41:47,350 --> 00:41:48,810
Thank you.

551
00:41:48,810 --> 00:41:51,870
- Enjoy your meal.
- Enjoy.

552
00:41:52,770 --> 00:41:58,760
♫ You are my little garden ♫

553
00:41:59,810 --> 00:42:03,520
♫ My sky, which has forgotten words ♫

554
00:42:03,520 --> 00:42:05,010
So,

555
00:42:06,490 --> 00:42:08,230
what will you do now?

556
00:42:08,230 --> 00:42:10,210
What can I do?

557
00:42:10,210 --> 00:42:12,170
I have to look for another job.

558
00:42:13,030 --> 00:42:14,660
Since it's come to this,

559
00:42:14,660 --> 00:42:18,960
I might as well try for a job
with higher pay and a bigger company.

560
00:42:18,960 --> 00:42:21,120
Since this industry has a high turnover,

561
00:42:21,120 --> 00:42:23,920
there will be places to interview.

562
00:42:23,920 --> 00:42:28,530
Wow. I almost feel betrayed.

563
00:42:28,530 --> 00:42:31,020
I worried for nothing, Ko Yeong Rye.

564
00:42:32,420 --> 00:42:35,020
Maybe it's for the best.

565
00:42:35,020 --> 00:42:37,970
Honestly, the manager didn't really like me,

566
00:42:37,970 --> 00:42:40,540
so it was a bit rough mentally.

567
00:42:40,540 --> 00:42:44,010
Working somewhere else
could be a blessing in disguise.

568
00:42:44,010 --> 00:42:47,480
Like my mom says, there's no food for a lazy man.

569
00:42:47,480 --> 00:42:51,610
I'll start fresh tomorrow and give it a shot.

570
00:42:51,610 --> 00:42:55,450
All right. I'll admit you're tough, so eat.

571
00:42:55,450 --> 00:42:57,260
The noodles will get soggy.

572
00:43:08,490 --> 00:43:10,700
You're not hungry, huh?

573
00:43:10,700 --> 00:43:12,680
Did you eat something by yourself?

574
00:43:13,580 --> 00:43:17,520
Yeah. B-But not alone.

575
00:43:17,520 --> 00:43:19,670
Not alone, huh?

576
00:43:19,670 --> 00:43:21,050
What?

577
00:43:22,190 --> 00:43:23,310
With Jong Hui?

578
00:43:23,310 --> 00:43:25,640
No, not Jong Hui.

579
00:43:28,100 --> 00:43:30,400
Have some more. Here.

580
00:43:34,200 --> 00:43:37,300
How's Ahjussi? Is he okay?

581
00:43:37,300 --> 00:43:40,350
Yeah. Thanks to you.

582
00:43:41,680 --> 00:43:45,020
We even went to the bathhouse
together this past weekend.

583
00:43:45,020 --> 00:43:48,570
I scrubbed his back for the first time.

584
00:43:51,200 --> 00:43:56,590
You're probably not worried,
but let me say this just in case.

585
00:43:56,590 --> 00:44:01,930
People trust you at a glance.

586
00:44:01,930 --> 00:44:05,480
Wherever you interview, you'll land it.

587
00:44:05,480 --> 00:44:07,970
It's so obvious that those are empty words.

588
00:44:07,970 --> 00:44:10,460
At least, make it sound convincing.

589
00:44:10,460 --> 00:44:12,100
Hey, I'm being serious.

590
00:44:12,100 --> 00:44:17,100
It's not just your first impression.
You can tell after a few words.

591
00:44:17,100 --> 00:44:23,500
You're sharp, and your facial
features are all well situated.

592
00:44:23,500 --> 00:44:27,100
So you look neat and tidy. What else is there?

593
00:44:27,100 --> 00:44:30,840
Hey. Don't try too hard and just eat.

594
00:44:32,500 --> 00:44:34,320
Eat up.

595
00:44:35,800 --> 00:44:38,000
- It's true!
- Hey.

596
00:44:38,000 --> 00:44:41,450
- I'm not-
- Don't talk with your mouth full.

597
00:44:44,200 --> 00:44:46,400
I'm not like that.

598
00:44:46,400 --> 00:44:49,230
[Michelle Beauty Salon]

599
00:44:49,230 --> 00:44:52,270
Be confident. Be calm.

600
00:44:53,120 --> 00:44:56,500
Ko Yeong Rye. You can do this!

601
00:44:57,310 --> 00:45:00,480
[Michelle Beauty Salon]

602
00:45:11,780 --> 00:45:14,120
[Resume]

603
00:45:14,120 --> 00:45:16,770
Why did you quit Jullee?

604
00:45:16,770 --> 00:45:18,470
Was it the pay?

605
00:45:18,470 --> 00:45:20,380
No.

606
00:45:20,380 --> 00:45:23,980
I was terminated because of a mistake I made.

607
00:45:23,980 --> 00:45:26,590
I like your honesty.

608
00:45:26,590 --> 00:45:29,180
Then, let me give you a scenario.

609
00:45:29,180 --> 00:45:31,370
Answer as you would.

610
00:45:31,370 --> 00:45:32,420
Okay.

611
00:45:32,420 --> 00:45:35,420
A woman who has just broken up
with her lover comes in

612
00:45:35,420 --> 00:45:39,200
and asks for the shortest cut possible.

613
00:45:39,200 --> 00:45:43,800
How would you handle it, Ms. Ko Yeong Rye?

614
00:45:46,100 --> 00:45:48,000
If it were me...

615
00:45:59,240 --> 00:46:01,280
Hey! Come over for some coffee.

616
00:46:01,280 --> 00:46:02,540
The vegetable store is buying.

617
00:46:02,540 --> 00:46:04,970
It's fine. You guys enjoy yourselves.

618
00:46:04,970 --> 00:46:06,490
I already had some earlier.

619
00:46:06,490 --> 00:46:08,010
All right.

620
00:46:14,330 --> 00:46:16,970
Where's Sparrow's Mill?

621
00:46:16,970 --> 00:46:19,710
Go about 20 meters straight ahead.

622
00:46:19,710 --> 00:46:22,150
Oh, okay. Thank you!

623
00:46:25,090 --> 00:46:27,140
For heaven's sake.

624
00:46:27,140 --> 00:46:29,540
Stop overreacting, will you?

625
00:46:29,540 --> 00:46:32,280
Either she'll get it or not.

626
00:46:32,280 --> 00:46:36,630
It's just one little interview.
No need to be so anxious.

627
00:46:38,670 --> 00:46:40,170
Mother.

628
00:46:40,170 --> 00:46:43,290
- What?
- You're holding the mallet backward.

629
00:46:44,220 --> 00:46:46,290
Either way,

630
00:46:46,290 --> 00:46:49,440
as long as the pollock gets whacked, right?

631
00:46:52,160 --> 00:46:54,700
But why isn't Noona back yet?

632
00:46:54,700 --> 00:46:56,590
Did the interview not go well?

633
00:46:56,590 --> 00:46:58,140
That can't happen.

634
00:46:58,140 --> 00:47:00,700
Unni has to get the job, so I get my allowance.

635
00:47:00,700 --> 00:47:03,290
When Yeong Rye comes in, don't make a big deal.

636
00:47:03,290 --> 00:47:05,080
Don't pressure her.

637
00:47:05,080 --> 00:47:06,560
Especially you, Ho Suk!

638
00:47:06,560 --> 00:47:08,430
Of course!

639
00:47:08,430 --> 00:47:10,600
I'm not an idiot.

640
00:47:10,600 --> 00:47:14,370
I've had a lifetime of reading the room, you know.

641
00:47:16,470 --> 00:47:18,310
- Hey, how'd it go?
- Did you get it? Are you hired?

642
00:47:18,310 --> 00:47:19,380
- Did you pass?
- Did you pass the interview?

643
00:47:19,380 --> 00:47:22,570
What are you all saying? One question at a time.

644
00:47:22,570 --> 00:47:25,870
Damn it. So what did they say? Are you hired?

645
00:47:25,870 --> 00:47:27,320
Huh? Did you pass?

646
00:47:27,320 --> 00:47:31,750
Yeah. I passed. I start tomorrow.

647
00:47:33,860 --> 00:47:36,380
- Aigoo, good job!
- Oh, gosh.

648
00:47:39,660 --> 00:47:42,840
Don't make any mistakes there.

649
00:47:42,840 --> 00:47:47,820
All right, then. Cheers to Yeong Rye
getting into Michelle!

650
00:47:47,820 --> 00:47:50,480
Cheers!

651
00:47:54,800 --> 00:47:57,030
That hits the spot.

652
00:47:58,230 --> 00:48:02,070
Isn't Michelle a much more successful,
top-tier hair salon

653
00:48:02,070 --> 00:48:04,220
in our country than Jullee?

654
00:48:04,220 --> 00:48:05,480
That's right.

655
00:48:05,480 --> 00:48:08,440
When Jullee hears this,
they'll go green with envy.

656
00:48:08,440 --> 00:48:09,650
Serves them right.

657
00:48:09,650 --> 00:48:11,960
Stop putting me on a pedestal.

658
00:48:11,960 --> 00:48:14,260
I'm still just a junior staff.

659
00:48:14,260 --> 00:48:16,190
Hey, staff or not,

660
00:48:16,190 --> 00:48:19,590
your title is a designer, and you
said the pay is better, too.

661
00:48:19,590 --> 00:48:22,250
That's a step up. What else is there to it?

662
00:48:22,250 --> 00:48:25,030
You're just happy my paycheck is
bigger, aren't you?

663
00:48:25,030 --> 00:48:26,800
Honestly.

664
00:48:26,800 --> 00:48:28,240
What the hell are you saying?

665
00:48:28,240 --> 00:48:31,400
If anyone here doesn't like money, step right up.

666
00:48:31,400 --> 00:48:32,780
Step right up!

667
00:48:32,780 --> 00:48:34,850
I like money, too.

668
00:48:34,850 --> 00:48:37,260
That goes without saying.

669
00:48:37,260 --> 00:48:39,360
Congratulations!

670
00:48:39,360 --> 00:48:41,770
Having a party without me?

671
00:48:41,770 --> 00:48:44,030
Jong Hui, you came?

672
00:48:44,030 --> 00:48:46,290
It's been a while, Jong Hui. Sit down.

673
00:48:46,290 --> 00:48:48,010
H-How did you find out?

674
00:48:48,010 --> 00:48:49,400
How else?

675
00:48:49,400 --> 00:48:53,270
I called because I heard you had
an interview, and Ho Suk told me.

676
00:48:53,270 --> 00:48:55,890
Congrats. I heard you landed somewhere better.

677
00:48:55,890 --> 00:48:57,880
No, it's not that big of a difference.

678
00:48:57,880 --> 00:48:59,800
How is it not a big difference?

679
00:48:59,800 --> 00:49:03,800
Like our money-loving Mother said,
the salary is more.

680
00:49:03,800 --> 00:49:07,800
Good grief, this brat. I raised a tiger cub.

681
00:49:07,800 --> 00:49:09,680
Starting tomorrow, don't eat my food.

682
00:49:09,680 --> 00:49:12,920
Gosh! Mother is holding food over my head.

683
00:49:12,920 --> 00:49:16,280
Oh, how sad. Oh, my gosh!

684
00:49:17,650 --> 00:49:19,600
I'll get that.

685
00:49:20,990 --> 00:49:23,490
Since Jong Hui is here,
let's raise our glasses again.

686
00:49:23,490 --> 00:49:25,230
- Cheers!
- Cheers, cheers!

687
00:49:25,230 --> 00:49:26,530
One, two, three!

688
00:49:26,530 --> 00:49:29,480
Cheers!

689
00:49:30,301 --> 00:49:31,400
Hello?

690
00:49:31,400 --> 00:49:33,910
Ko Yeong Rye, how did it go?

691
00:49:33,910 --> 00:49:36,040
What do you think?

692
00:49:36,040 --> 00:49:37,470
You got it.

693
00:49:37,470 --> 00:49:38,970
You got hired, didn't you?

694
00:49:38,970 --> 00:49:40,710
Bingo.

695
00:49:42,430 --> 00:49:45,580
Gosh, congrats! See? What did I tell you?

696
00:49:45,580 --> 00:49:47,240
I told you, you'd pass for sure.

697
00:49:47,240 --> 00:49:49,360
I told you it was a sure thing.

698
00:49:49,360 --> 00:49:52,140
Yeah. They say words have power.

699
00:49:52,140 --> 00:49:56,190
I think it's because you got your hopes up for me.

700
00:49:56,190 --> 00:49:59,100
Thanks, Han Jae Pil.

701
00:49:59,100 --> 00:50:03,540
Honestly, all day while I was eating,
seeing patients,

702
00:50:03,540 --> 00:50:06,500
and even while getting chewed out
by a senior, I kept praying.

703
00:50:06,500 --> 00:50:08,490
"Please let Ko Yeong Rye pass.

704
00:50:08,490 --> 00:50:11,510
Ko Yeong Rye must pass. She must pass."

705
00:50:11,510 --> 00:50:13,810
I'm even more thankful.

706
00:50:13,810 --> 00:50:16,550
Hey, you're not on call tonight, right?

707
00:50:16,550 --> 00:50:18,020
Want to come over after?

708
00:50:18,020 --> 00:50:20,110
We're having a party right now.

709
00:50:20,110 --> 00:50:22,790
I really want to,

710
00:50:22,790 --> 00:50:24,790
but I've got plans.

711
00:50:34,410 --> 00:50:38,060
Seriously. I told you I already had plans.

712
00:50:38,060 --> 00:50:40,850
If you want to drink that much, drink alone.

713
00:50:40,850 --> 00:50:44,640
Hey. What's the fun in drinking alone?

714
00:50:44,640 --> 00:50:47,370
I'm already feeling down as it is.

715
00:50:47,370 --> 00:50:48,820
Why?

716
00:50:48,820 --> 00:50:51,670
What have you got to be down about?

717
00:50:53,420 --> 00:50:55,980
I can't tell you, punk.

718
00:50:59,080 --> 00:51:00,790
Who were you meeting, anyway?

719
00:51:00,790 --> 00:51:02,380
Tell them to come here if it's okay.

720
00:51:02,380 --> 00:51:04,330
I already did.

721
00:51:04,330 --> 00:51:05,690
Yeah?

722
00:51:06,590 --> 00:51:08,350
There he is.

723
00:51:13,800 --> 00:51:17,900
You were meeting with Han Jae Pil?

724
00:51:30,100 --> 00:51:36,720
Actually, I was debating
whether or not to meet you.

725
00:51:36,720 --> 00:51:39,140
You were?

726
00:51:39,140 --> 00:51:40,500
Why?

727
00:51:40,500 --> 00:51:42,370
Han Jae Pil,

728
00:51:43,760 --> 00:51:45,810
pick a lane.

729
00:51:47,400 --> 00:51:51,700
Not sure if you've noticed,
but I care about Yeong Rye a lot.

730
00:51:53,420 --> 00:51:58,170
But ever since your friend Jong Hui
showed up, I've been confused.

731
00:51:59,140 --> 00:52:01,000
Where your heart lies.

732
00:52:02,470 --> 00:52:07,300
So, state your position clearly. Pick a lane.

733
00:52:10,300 --> 00:52:15,400
If you hesitate, I'm going to floor it.

734
00:52:21,150 --> 00:52:24,220
I'm warning you, man to man.

735
00:52:25,460 --> 00:52:27,060
Got it?

736
00:52:35,100 --> 00:52:37,100
Are you fighting? What's with the vibe?

737
00:52:37,100 --> 00:52:40,030
Fighting? Are we kids? Hey, let's drink.

738
00:53:04,440 --> 00:53:06,690
Mom, I'm taking off.

739
00:53:06,690 --> 00:53:10,150
Aigoo, my daughter. It's your first day.

740
00:53:10,150 --> 00:53:12,100
Is it obvious I'm really nervous?

741
00:53:12,100 --> 00:53:13,290
Very.

742
00:53:13,290 --> 00:53:15,870
Relax your face.

743
00:53:15,870 --> 00:53:18,520
Jobs are all the same. What's the big deal?

744
00:53:18,520 --> 00:53:20,060
Don't worry and go.

745
00:53:20,060 --> 00:53:23,670
If you don't know something, just ask as you go.

746
00:53:23,670 --> 00:53:25,790
You needed a good night's sleep,

747
00:53:25,790 --> 00:53:28,140
but you didn't, did you?

748
00:53:28,140 --> 00:53:30,900
Because those guys were so disruptive.

749
00:54:16,380 --> 00:54:17,830
You're here, Ko Yeong Rye.

750
00:54:17,830 --> 00:54:20,160
Hello! Good morning.

751
00:54:20,160 --> 00:54:21,800
Get changed and come out.

752
00:54:21,800 --> 00:54:24,500
- I'll tell you what you need to do.
- Okay.

753
00:54:38,340 --> 00:54:40,600
[Ko Yeong Rye]

754
00:54:45,680 --> 00:54:47,300
Come this way.

755
00:54:49,140 --> 00:54:51,300
While you're getting adjusted,

756
00:54:51,300 --> 00:54:54,690
observe how the salon operates
and support where you can.

757
00:54:54,690 --> 00:54:57,770
All staff must gather 10 minutes before opening

758
00:54:57,770 --> 00:55:00,990
for a briefing on the day's
schedule. Remember that.

759
00:55:00,990 --> 00:55:04,170
As for your specific role...

760
00:55:05,100 --> 00:55:08,470
Let's discuss it after this week. Okay?

761
00:55:08,470 --> 00:55:09,920
Okay.

762
00:55:16,270 --> 00:55:19,040
Good morning.

763
00:55:19,040 --> 00:55:22,940
First, double-check all booked clients carefully.

764
00:55:22,940 --> 00:55:24,950
We've got two outside events today, right?

765
00:55:24,950 --> 00:55:27,020
The CF shoot over in Dasan.

766
00:55:27,020 --> 00:55:28,820
- Manager Han's team?
- Yes.

767
00:55:28,820 --> 00:55:30,790
Make sure they stick to the agreed-upon times.

768
00:55:30,790 --> 00:55:34,000
"Just wing it, good enough" approach
doesn't fly anymore.

769
00:55:34,000 --> 00:55:36,110
We need to make that clear.

770
00:55:36,110 --> 00:55:39,820
The two-day beauty seminar in Dongincheon.

771
00:55:39,820 --> 00:55:43,090
I'll be there myself, so no worries.

772
00:55:43,090 --> 00:55:45,120
Manager Oh, what about staffing?

773
00:55:45,120 --> 00:55:47,400
Stylists Yoon Ju and Jeong Hui are set to go.

774
00:55:47,400 --> 00:55:49,340
Including me, that's three.

775
00:55:49,340 --> 00:55:51,500
Is that enough?

776
00:55:51,500 --> 00:55:52,820
Take the new hire.

777
00:55:52,820 --> 00:55:55,520
Big events are all about experience.

778
00:55:55,520 --> 00:55:57,060
That's all.

779
00:56:00,630 --> 00:56:02,620
Fieldwork on her first day?

780
00:56:02,620 --> 00:56:04,190
How nice.

781
00:56:04,190 --> 00:56:06,580
What is this, special treatment?

782
00:56:10,900 --> 00:56:12,770
You heard that, right?

783
00:56:12,770 --> 00:56:14,800
The event starts in the afternoon,

784
00:56:14,800 --> 00:56:17,300
so go early and set everything up.

785
00:56:17,300 --> 00:56:18,700
Okay.

786
00:56:34,400 --> 00:56:36,360
Ahjussi!

787
00:56:53,010 --> 00:56:56,590
I let you crash here once,
and it's become a habit.

788
00:56:56,590 --> 00:56:59,910
If you got wasted, you should head home quietly.

789
00:56:59,910 --> 00:57:02,040
Why do you keep barging over here?

790
00:57:02,040 --> 00:57:04,330
I'm sorry, Mother.

791
00:57:04,330 --> 00:57:07,430
Nothing beats your dried
pollock soup for a hangover.

792
00:57:08,640 --> 00:57:11,530
Yes, I agree.

793
00:57:12,750 --> 00:57:14,770
I finally feel my stomach settling.

794
00:57:14,770 --> 00:57:16,470
Why are you grabbing...

795
00:57:16,470 --> 00:57:19,070
What the hell? Do I grab it, too?

796
00:57:19,070 --> 00:57:21,630
- What the hell?
- That's enough.

797
00:57:21,630 --> 00:57:23,060
You're flattering me.

798
00:57:23,060 --> 00:57:25,780
Eat quickly and go.

799
00:57:25,780 --> 00:57:28,100
Jae Pil, you have to get to the hospital, right?

800
00:57:28,100 --> 00:57:32,100
Yes, that's right.
But I can go in a little late today.

801
00:57:34,810 --> 00:57:37,340
Sit, I'll get it.

802
00:57:39,920 --> 00:57:41,780
Yes. This is Yeong Sik's Baekban.

803
00:57:41,780 --> 00:57:44,530
Mom, is Sang Cheol in his store?

804
00:57:44,530 --> 00:57:46,740
I'm in a rush. Could I catch a ride with him?

805
00:57:46,740 --> 00:57:49,440
He went out to collect payments.

806
00:57:49,440 --> 00:57:51,310
Why do you need a ride?

807
00:57:51,310 --> 00:57:53,920
Aren't you starting at Michelle today?

808
00:57:53,920 --> 00:57:56,920
Yes, but I have to get to Dongincheon right away.

809
00:57:56,920 --> 00:57:59,080
But I missed the bus at the terminal.

810
00:57:59,080 --> 00:58:01,460
And the taxis won't go outside Seoul.

811
00:58:02,330 --> 00:58:06,040
Okay, I'll try to grab another taxi.
I'm hanging up.

812
00:58:06,040 --> 00:58:07,330
Oh, no.

813
00:58:07,330 --> 00:58:11,340
What kind of shop sends a kid all the way
to Dongincheon on her first day?

814
00:58:11,340 --> 00:58:13,100
Goodness...

815
00:58:13,100 --> 00:58:15,300
I'll take her, Mother.

816
00:58:15,300 --> 00:58:18,900
- Your food-
- My car is around the corner.

817
00:58:18,900 --> 00:58:21,010
Okay, sure.

818
00:58:21,010 --> 00:58:22,690
That guy...

819
00:58:30,290 --> 00:58:32,870
[Taxi Stop]

820
00:58:43,780 --> 00:58:46,970
Yeong Rye, it's me again. Get in.

821
00:58:54,360 --> 00:58:57,270
You can breathe normally again.

822
00:59:23,550 --> 00:59:27,300
Han Jae Pil, pick a lane.

823
00:59:27,300 --> 00:59:32,400
If you hesitate, I'm going to floor it.

824
00:59:32,400 --> 00:59:35,630
I'm warning you, man to man.

825
00:59:41,340 --> 00:59:42,990
Please take a deep breath.

826
00:59:42,990 --> 00:59:48,060
[Restore law and order]

827
00:59:49,720 --> 00:59:54,690
[Correctional]

828
01:00:24,940 --> 01:00:27,820
- Mom, let's go. Let's go.
- Let's go...

829
01:00:53,120 --> 01:00:57,670
I wanted to treat you and your daughter to a meal.

830
01:00:57,670 --> 01:00:59,760
Given what happened last time,

831
01:00:59,760 --> 01:01:04,390
I asked to see you because there's
something I'd like to discuss.

832
01:01:05,230 --> 01:01:07,330
You didn't have to do this.

833
01:01:07,330 --> 01:01:09,660
What is it you wanted to say?

834
01:01:09,660 --> 01:01:11,760
How should I put this?

835
01:01:11,760 --> 01:01:17,690
I'd like to make a proposal, if I may.

836
01:01:17,690 --> 01:01:22,540
The registration period for Miss Korea
is coming up soon.

837
01:01:22,540 --> 01:01:28,360
Our salon has been weighing various candidates.

838
01:01:29,300 --> 01:01:31,270
From the moment I saw her,

839
01:01:31,270 --> 01:01:35,200
